# Design system

The canonical tokens and component rules live in `app/globals.css` (`:root`, `@theme inline`, `.ds-*` classes). **Source values** use `--palette-*` (colors) and `--ds-*` (radius, elevation shadows); `@theme` maps Tailwind `--color-*`, `--radius-*`, and `--shadow-*` utilities from those. **Use only values defined there** (or the same literals from the written spec). Do not invent spacing, radii, colors, motion, or shadows outside that file.

- **Layout**: Use `.ds-container` and `.ds-grid` for the 1440px / 16-col pattern (gutter 8px). Page inline padding is `--ds-container-margin-inline` (16px below `sm`, 24px from `sm` up; navbar uses the same token). Tailwind spacing uses `--spacing-*` from the scale in `globals.css`.
- **Container text**: Inside `.ds-container`, wrap typographic content (headings, paragraphs, lists, etc.) in `.ds-container-text` — a column with `gap` and padding (`gap-4`, `px-4` / `pt-5`, `sm:px-6` / `sm:pt-6` via tokens in `globals.css`). Optional band surfaces: `.ds-container-surface-warm-gradient` (orange → yellow → red gradient, inverse text).
- **Border-radius**: All top-level content blocks (navbar, image containers, cards, section surfaces) use `--ds-container-radius` (`rounded-lg`, 12px). Use this as the default for any new container or content surface — keep them visually consistent.
- **Typography**: Metropolis via `--font-metropolis` (all UI). Use `.ds-text-caption` through `.ds-text-display` or match those CSS variables exactly.
- **Components**: Prefer `.ds-btn`, `.ds-btn-primary`, `.ds-card`, `.ds-input`, modal/dropdown/tooltip/toast classes in `globals.css` for spec-aligned behavior (focus, hover, elevation).
- **Icons**: `lucide-react`, stroke width 2, default size 20px (`--size-icon-md`), round caps — per project spec.
- **Accessibility**: Focus rings per spec (accent outline on buttons/links; primary border + ring on inputs — never both on one element). Honor `prefers-reduced-motion` (already global).

When adding UI, extend patterns in `globals.css` rather than hard-coding one-off design values.
